SIMPLE: pug
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pug
<hw>Pug</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Pugged</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pugging</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. G. <ets>pucken</ets> to
thump. beat.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To mix and stir when wet, as clay for bricks,
pottery, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To fill or stop with clay by tamping; to fill in or
spread with mortar, as a floor or partition, for the purpose of
deadening sound. See <er>Pugging</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pug</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pug
<hw>Pug</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Tempered clay; clay
moistened and worked so as to be plastic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A pug mill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pug mill</b></col>, <cd>a kind of mill for grinding and
mixing clay, either for brickmaking or the fine arts; a clay mill. It
consists essentially of an upright shaft armed with projecting knives,
which is caused to revolve in a hollow cylinder, tub, or vat, in which
the clay is placed.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pug</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Pug
<hw>Pug</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted fr. <ets>puck</ets>. See
<er>Puck</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An elf, or a hobgoblin; also same
as <er>Puck</er>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A name for a monkey.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A name for a fox.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>C. Kingsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An intimate; a crony; a dear one.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Lyly.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Chaff; the refuse of grain.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>A prostitute.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cotgrave.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a small breed of pet dogs
having a short nose and head; a pug dog.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>8.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any geometrid moth of the genus
<gen>Eupithecia</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pug</ent>⟦br⟧
